7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 673, L.D. 1720, “An Act Regarding
10 Benefits and Training for Long-term Care Workers”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, Regarding Certified Nursing Assistant Examinations'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. Department of Health and Human Services to offer translated
15 certified nursing assistant examinations. Resolved: That the Department of Health
16 and Human Services shall offer certified nursing assistant examinations in several
17 languages. The department's division of licensing and certification shall collaborate with
18 experts and relevant stakeholders to improve access to certification for persons who do not
19 speak English by offering, at a minimum, the certified nursing assistant written
20 examination under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 32, chapter 31 in French, Spanish,
21 Cantonese, Mandarin and Filipino. The department may determine the most appropriate
22 dialect or variant of each language in consultation with subject matter experts to ensure
23 accuracy and cultural appropriateness. The department shall develop and make available
24 written examinations under this section by January 1, 2026.
25 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
26 appropriations and allocations are made.
27 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
28 Division of Licensing and Certification Z036
29 Initiative: Provides funding for contracted services to translate the certified nursing
30 assistant written examination into 5 languages by January 1, 2026 and to translate future
31 revisions to the exam.
32 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
33 All Other $40,570 $13,524
